---
import BaseLayout from '../components/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout 
    title="What Is a Data Center? The Engine of the Modern World"
    description="Learn how data centers power everyday life, from healthcare to AI, and why they are the essential infrastructure of the 21st century."
>
    <!-- Page Header -->
    <div class="bg-slate-900 border-b border-tech-blue/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-br from-pine-green/80 to-tech-blue/80 z-0 mix-blend-multiply"></div>
        <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-[url('https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1558494949-ef010cbdcc31?q=80&w=2668&auto=format&fit=crop')] bg-cover bg-center z-0 opacity-40 mix-blend-overlay"></div>
        <div class="relative z-10 max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-20 lg:py-24">
            <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-bold text-white mb-6 tracking-tight">What Is a Data Center? <span class="text-transparent bg-clip-text bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-300 to-teal-300 block mt-3">The Engine of the Modern World</span></h1>
            <p class="text-xl text-slate-200 max-w-3xl leading-relaxed font-light">
                Demystifying the incredible facilities that act as the true backbone of our modern, interconnected lives.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Main Content -->
    <section class="py-16 lg:py-24 bg-white">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
            
            <div class="prose prose-lg prose-slate max-w-none mb-16">
                <p class="text-2xl leading-relaxed mb-10 text-slate-700 font-medium">
                    A data center is the physical facility that stores, processes, and transmits the data that powers the modern world. It is the home of the cloud, the backbone of the internet, and the engine of artificial intelligence. Every time you stream a movie, attend a telehealth appointment, check the weather, use GPS navigation, send an email, or work remotely, you are relying on a data center to process and deliver that information to you in milliseconds.
                </p>

                <p class="leading-relaxed text-slate-600">
                    Inside a data center are thousands of specialized computers called servers, alongside the networking equipment, cooling systems, and power infrastructure required to keep them running continuously, 24 hours a day, 365 days a year. Because our modern lives depend on these systems, data centers are built to be extraordinarily reliable. They often achieve what the industry calls "five nines" uptime, meaning they are operational <strong class="text-slate-900 font-bold bg-tech-blue/10 px-2 py-1 rounded">99.999% of the time</strong>.
                </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Infographic Placeholder Section -->
            <div class="my-20 bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 rounded-[2rem] p-8 lg:p-16 shadow-lg text-center relative overflow-hidden">
                <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 w-64 h-64 bg-tech-blue/5 rounded-full blur-3xl -translate-y-1/2 translate-x-1/2"></div>
                <div class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 w-64 h-64 bg-pine-green/5 rounded-full blur-3xl translate-y-1/2 -translate-x-1/2"></div>
                
                <div class="relative z-10">
                    <div class="w-20 h-20 bg-white shadow-md rounded-2xl flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-8 text-tech-blue ring-1 ring-slate-100">
                        <svg class="w-10 h-10" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 11H5m14 0a2 2 0 012 2v6a2 2 0 01-2 2H5a2 2 0 01-2-2v-6a2 2 0 012-2m14 0V9a2 2 0 00-2-2M5 11V9a2 2 0 002-2m0 0V5a2 2 0 012-2h6a2 2 0 012 2v2M7 7h10" />
                        </svg>
                    </div>
                    <h3 class="text-2xl lg:text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4 tracking-tight">The Invisible Flow of Innovation</h3>
                    <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-12">
                        Data travels continuously from your device, across vast fiber optic networks, directly into the servers housed in secure data centers, and back again in a fraction of a second.
                    </p>
                    
                    <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row items-center justify-center space-y-6 md:space-y-0 md:space-x-6">
                        <!-- Workflow visualization -->
                        <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-sm border border-slate-100 w-full flex-1">
                            <span class="block text-5xl mb-4">📱</span>
                            <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-lg">Your Devices</h4>
                            <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 mt-2">Streaming, Banking, Medical</p>
                        </div>
                        
                        <div class="text-tech-blue/40 flex flex-col items-center">
                            <svg class="w-10 h-10 hidden md:block" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                               <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 8l4 4m0 0l-4 4m4-4H3" />
                            </svg>
                            <span class="text-xs font-bold tracking-widest uppercase my-2 text-slate-400">Milliseconds</span>
                            <svg class="w-10 h-10 hidden md:block" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                               <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M7 16l-4-4m0 0l4-4m-4 4h18" />
                            </svg>
                            
                            <svg class="w-8 h-8 md:hidden my-2" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 14l-7 7m0 0l-7-7m7 7V3" />
                            </svg>
                        </div>
                        
                        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-tech-blue to-blue-800 p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-lg border border-transparent w-full flex-1 text-white relative overflow-hidden">
                            <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 w-32 h-32 bg-white/10 rounded-full blur-2xl -translate-y-1/2 translate-x-1/2"></div>
                            <span class="block text-5xl mb-4 relative z-10">🏢</span>
                            <h4 class="font-bold text-white text-lg relative z-10">Secure Data Center</h4>
                            <p class="text-sm text-blue-200 mt-2 relative z-10">Instant Processing & Storage</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="prose prose-lg prose-slate max-w-none">
                <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6 text-slate-900 tracking-tight">The Infrastructure of the 21st Century</h2>
                <p class="leading-relaxed mb-6 text-slate-600">
                    Throughout history, new infrastructure has consistently unlocked new eras of prosperity. Data centers are the essential infrastructure of the 21st century in the exact same way that railroads were the essential infrastructure of the 19th century, and the interstate highway system was the essential infrastructure of the 20th century. 
                </p>
                <p class="leading-relaxed mb-8 text-slate-600">
                    Just as those historic investments transformed rural economies and connected communities to national prosperity, data centers are doing the same today, ensuring that the technology of tomorrow is rooted right here in our communities.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
    <!-- HISTORY: From Room-Sized Machines to the Engine of the Internet   -->
    <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->

    <!-- Section Header -->
    <section class="py-20 lg:py-28 bg-slate-50 relative overflow-hidden" id="history">
        <div class="absolute top-0 left-0 w-full h-1 bg-gradient-to-r from-tech-blue via-pine-green to-amber-warm"></div>
        <div class="absolute bottom-0 right-0 w-[600px] h-[600px] bg-tech-blue/5 rounded-full blur-[120px] translate-x-1/3 translate-y-1/3 pointer-events-none"></div>
        <div class="absolute top-0 left-0 w-[400px] h-[400px] bg-pine-green/5 rounded-full blur-[100px] -translate-x-1/3 -translate-y-1/3 pointer-events-none"></div>

        <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 relative z-10">
            <div class="text-center max-w-4xl mx-auto mb-20">
                <span class="inline-block px-5 py-2 rounded-full bg-tech-blue/10 text-tech-blue font-bold tracking-widest uppercase text-xs mb-6 border border-tech-blue/20">The Full Story</span>
                <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900 mb-6 heading-display">From Room-Sized Machines to the Engine of the Internet</h2>
                <p class="text-xl text-slate-600 leading-relaxed font-light max-w-3xl mx-auto">
                    Almost everything you did online today passed through a data center. The text you sent, the payment you made, the show you streamed, the search you ran, the map that found your route home. These buildings are the quiet infrastructure of modern life, and most people have never seen one.
                </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Timeline -->
            <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
                <!-- Timeline spine (desktop only) -->
                <div class="hidden lg:block absolute left-1/2 top-0 bottom-0 w-px bg-gradient-to-b from-transparent via-tech-blue/20 to-transparent" style="margin-left: -0.5px;"></div>

                <!-- Era 1: 1940s -->
                <div class="relative grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-8 lg:gap-16 mb-16 lg:mb-24">
                    <div class="lg:text-right">
                        <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 text-amber-800 px-4 py-1.5 rounded-full text-sm font-bold tracking-wide mb-6">
                            <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 8v4l3 3m6-3a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" /></svg>
                            1940s – 1960s
                        </div>
                        <h3 class="text-2xl lg:text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4 tracking-tight">Where It All Started: The First Computer Rooms</h3>
                        <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
                            The story begins in the 1940s with machines like ENIAC, completed in 1945. ENIAC filled a large room, weighed about 30 tons, and used thousands of vacuum tubes. It needed dedicated power, constant cooling, and a controlled, secured space just to function. That special-purpose room was the ancestor of the modern data center: a place built around the machine rather than the people.
                        </p>
                        <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
                            Through the 1950s and 1960s, the mainframe era took hold. Businesses, banks, universities, and government agencies installed large IBM and competitor systems in purpose-built computer rooms. This is when many of the design ideas we still use were born: raised floors to route cabling and push cool air, tight climate control, backup power, and restricted access. Computing was centralized because the machines were rare, enormous, and expensive.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="flex items-center">
                        <div class="bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-3xl p-8 shadow-sm w-full relative overflow-hidden group hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow duration-300">
                            <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 w-32 h-32 bg-amber-500/5 rounded-full blur-2xl -translate-y-1/2 translate-x-1/2"></div>
                            <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-6">
                                <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-amber-50 rounded-2xl flex items-center justify-center text-3xl flex-shrink-0 group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform">🖥️</div>
                                <div>
                                    <p class="text-4xl font-black text-amber-600">30 tons</p>
                                    <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 font-medium">Weight of ENIAC (1945)</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
                                <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-amber-50 rounded-2xl flex items-center justify-center text-3xl flex-shrink-0 group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform">💡</div>
                                <div>
                                    <p class="text-4xl font-black text-amber-600">18,000</p>
                                    <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 font-medium">Vacuum tubes in one machine</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Era 2: 1980s–1990s -->
                <div class="relative grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-8 lg:gap-16 mb-16 lg:mb-24">
                    <div class="lg:order-2">
                        <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-tech-blue/10 border border-tech-blue/20 text-tech-blue px-4 py-1.5 rounded-full text-sm font-bold tracking-wide mb-6">
                            <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M4 4v5h.582m15.356 2A8.001 8.001 0 004.582 9m0 0H9m11 11v-5h-.581m0 0a8.003 8.003 0 01-15.357-2m15.357 2H15" /></svg>
                            1980s – 1990s
                        </div>
                        <h3 class="text-2xl lg:text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4 tracking-tight">The Detour and the Comeback</h3>
                        <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
                            When the personal computer arrived in the 1980s, computing scattered. Power moved out of the central room and onto millions of desktops. For a while, the big centralized computer room looked like yesterday's idea.
                        </p>
                        <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
                            The internet changed everything back. As the 1990s progressed and the World Wide Web went mainstream, all those desktops and businesses needed somewhere to connect, host websites, and exchange data reliably around the clock. The modern term "data center" took hold in this period. Companies that could not afford to build and staff their own facilities began renting space in shared "colocation" centers, and a whole industry of internet hosting was born. The dot-com boom of the late 1990s drove a massive buildout of server farms.
                        </p>
                        <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
                            By the mid-2000s the industry had matured enough to need standards. Design and reliability frameworks such as the TIA-942 standard and the Uptime Institute's Tier classifications gave operators a common language for how resilient a facility was, from basic setups to fully fault-tolerant designs that aim for near-continuous uptime.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="flex items-center lg:order-1">
                        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-tech-blue to-blue-800 rounded-3xl p-8 shadow-xl w-full text-white relative overflow-hidden group">
                            <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 w-48 h-48 bg-white/10 rounded-full blur-3xl -translate-y-1/2 translate-x-1/2"></div>
                            <h4 class="text-lg font-bold text-blue-200 uppercase tracking-wider mb-6 relative z-10">Key Milestones</h4>
                            <div class="space-y-5 relative z-10">
                                <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
                                    <span class="w-8 h-8 bg-white/20 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 text-sm font-bold">🌐</span>
                                    <div>
                                        <p class="font-bold text-white">World Wide Web Goes Mainstream</p>
                                        <p class="text-sm text-blue-200">Every business needed somewhere to host</p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
                                    <span class="w-8 h-8 bg-white/20 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 text-sm font-bold">🏢</span>
                                    <div>
                                        <p class="font-bold text-white">Colocation Centers Born</p>
                                        <p class="text-sm text-blue-200">Shared facilities for companies of every size</p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
                                    <span class="w-8 h-8 bg-white/20 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 text-sm font-bold">📊</span>
                                    <div>
                                        <p class="font-bold text-white">TIA-942 & Tier Standards</p>
                                        <p class="text-sm text-blue-200">Common language for reliability & resilience</p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Era 3: 2006 to Today -->
                <div class="relative grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-8 lg:gap-16 mb-16 lg:mb-24">
                    <div class="lg:text-right">
                        <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-pine-green/10 border border-pine-green/20 text-pine-green px-4 py-1.5 rounded-full text-sm font-bold tracking-wide mb-6">
                            <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 7h8m0 0v8m0-8l-8 8-4-4-6 6" /></svg>
                            2006 – Today
                        </div>
                        <h3 class="text-2xl lg:text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4 tracking-tight">The Cloud and Hyperscale Era</h3>
                        <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
                            The next leap was the cloud. When Amazon Web Services launched in 2006, followed by Google and Microsoft Azure, the model flipped again. Instead of every company owning servers, they could rent computing power on demand from a handful of giant providers. Those providers built "hyperscale" data centers: enormous, highly automated, extremely efficient campuses that can span millions of square feet.
                        </p>
                        <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
                            Then came artificial intelligence. Training and running modern AI models requires unprecedented amounts of specialized computing, and that demand has set off the largest infrastructure expansion the industry has ever seen. Statista and other market trackers describe data centers as the heart of the AI revolution, and the world now has an estimated 11,000 to 12,000 of them across more than 170 countries.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="flex items-center">
                        <div class="bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-3xl p-8 shadow-sm w-full relative overflow-hidden group hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow duration-300">
                            <div class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 w-32 h-32 bg-pine-green/5 rounded-full blur-2xl translate-y-1/2 -translate-x-1/2"></div>
                            <div class="space-y-6 relative z-10">
                                <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
                                    <div class="w-14 h-14 bg-pine-green/10 rounded-2xl flex items-center justify-center text-2xl flex-shrink-0 group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform">☁️</div>
                                    <div>
                                        <p class="text-3xl font-black text-pine-green">2006</p>
                                        <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 font-medium">AWS launched the cloud era</p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
                                    <div class="w-14 h-14 bg-pine-green/10 rounded-2xl flex items-center justify-center text-2xl flex-shrink-0 group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform">🌍</div>
                                    <div>
                                        <p class="text-3xl font-black text-pine-green">12,000+</p>
                                        <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 font-medium">Data centers worldwide today</p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
                                    <div class="w-14 h-14 bg-pine-green/10 rounded-2xl flex items-center justify-center text-2xl flex-shrink-0 group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform">🤖</div>
                                    <div>
                                        <p class="text-3xl font-black text-pine-green">170+</p>
                                        <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 font-medium">Countries with facilities</p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- What Data Centers Actually Do -->
    <section class="py-20 lg:py-28 bg-white relative">
        <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
            <div class="text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-16">
                <span class="inline-block px-5 py-2 rounded-full bg-pine-green/10 text-pine-green font-bold tracking-widest uppercase text-xs mb-6 border border-pine-green/20">Core Functions</span>
                <h2 class="text-3xl lg:text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900 mb-6">What Data Centers Actually Do</h2>
                <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
                    Strip away the jargon and a data center is a highly reliable building full of servers, storage systems, and networking gear, supported by robust power, cooling, and security. Its job is to store, process, and move digital information without interruption. When these facilities work well, you never think about them. <strong class="text-slate-900">That invisibility is the point.</strong>
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6 max-w-6xl mx-auto">
                <!-- Everyday Internet -->
                <div class="bg-slate-50 p-8 rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 hover:shadow-xl hover:border-tech-blue/40 transition-all duration-300 group cursor-default relative overflow-hidden">
                    <div class="w-14 h-14 bg-tech-blue/10 rounded-2xl flex items-center justify-center mb-5 text-tech-blue group-hover:bg-tech-blue group-hover:text-white transition-colors duration-300">
                        <svg class="w-7 h-7" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M21 12a9 9 0 01-9 9m9-9a9 9 0 00-9-9m9 9H3m9 9a9 9 0 01-9-9m9 9c1.657 0 3-4.03 3-9s-1.343-9-3-9m0 18c-1.657 0-3-4.03-3-9s1.343-9 3-9m-9 9a9 9 0 019-9" /></svg>
                    </div>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">The Everyday Internet</h3>
                    <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Websites, email, search, social media, and streaming video — every click and scroll passes through a data center.</p>
                    <div class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 w-full h-1 bg-gradient-to-r from-tech-blue to-blue-400 transform scale-x-0 group-hover:scale-x-100 origin-left transition-transform duration-300"></div>
                </div>
                <!-- Cloud Computing -->
                <div class="bg-slate-50 p-8 rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 hover:shadow-xl hover:border-blue-500/40 transition-all duration-300 group cursor-default relative overflow-hidden">
                    <div class="w-14 h-14 bg-blue-500/10 rounded-2xl flex items-center justify-center mb-5 text-blue-500 group-hover:bg-blue-500 group-hover:text-white transition-colors duration-300">
                        <svg class="w-7 h-7" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M3 15a4 4 0 004 4h9a5 5 0 10-.1-9.999 5.002 5.002 0 10-9.78 2.096A4.001 4.001 0 003 15z" /></svg>
                    </div>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">Cloud Computing</h3>
                    <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">The software, storage, and tools that businesses of every size now rent instead of owning — all hosted in data centers.</p>
                    <div class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 w-full h-1 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-500 to-cyan-400 transform scale-x-0 group-hover:scale-x-100 origin-left transition-transform duration-300"></div>
                </div>
                <!-- Commerce & Finance -->
                <div class="bg-slate-50 p-8 rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 hover:shadow-xl hover:border-emerald-500/40 transition-all duration-300 group cursor-default relative overflow-hidden">
                    <div class="w-14 h-14 bg-emerald-500/10 rounded-2xl flex items-center justify-center mb-5 text-emerald-500 group-hover:bg-emerald-500 group-hover:text-white transition-colors duration-300">
                        <svg class="w-7 h-7" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 8c-1.657 0-3 .895-3 2s1.343 2 3 2 3 .895 3 2-1.343 2-3 2m0-8c1.11 0 2.08.402 2.599 1M12 8V7m0 1v8m0 0v1m0-1c-1.11 0-2.08-.402-2.599-1M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" /></svg>
                    </div>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">Commerce & Finance</h3>
                    <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Online shopping, card payments, banking, and systems that clear trillions of dollars in transactions every day.</p>
                    <div class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 w-full h-1 bg-gradient-to-r from-emerald-500 to-green-400 transform scale-x-0 group-hover:scale-x-100 origin-left transition-transform duration-300"></div>
                </div>
                <!-- Critical Services -->
                <div class="bg-slate-50 p-8 rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 hover:shadow-xl hover:border-amber-500/40 transition-all duration-300 group cursor-default relative overflow-hidden">
                    <div class="w-14 h-14 bg-amber-500/10 rounded-2xl flex items-center justify-center mb-5 text-amber-500 group-hover:bg-amber-500 group-hover:text-white transition-colors duration-300">
